✘ `?` can only be used in a function that returns `Result` (or `Option`). It hands the error back to the caller on failure, so this function's signature must allow failure: declare it `As Result<T>`, or handle the error here with `Match` over `Ok`/`Err`.
⚠ [line 8] Function 'MightFail' is 'mightfail' on the Rust side — one rule: a VBR name is its lowercase self in Rust.